  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Given a positive integer NNN, find two positive integers AAA and BBB, such that A−B=NA - B = NA−B=N and the number of **distinct** prime factors of AAA and BBB are equal. If there exist multiple pairs of values of AAA and BBB satisfying the given conditions, you can output any one of them.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nFirst line will contain TTT, number of testcases. Then the testcases follow.\nEach testcase contains of a single line of input, integer NNN.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each testcase, output in a single line two space separated integers AAA and BBB.\nIf there are multiple answers, you can output any one of them.",
    "constraints": [
      "1≤T≤10001 \\leq T \\leq 10001≤T≤1000",
      "1≤N≤10161 \\leq N \\leq 10^{16}1≤N≤1016",
      "1≤A,B≤10181 \\leq A, B \\leq 10^{18}1≤A,B≤1018",
      "Subtasks",
      "Subtask 1 (100 points): Original constraints"
    ],
